irish lottery scam with standard chartered bank standard chartered bank is supposed to be the payor for the irish lottery i have won but never entered any one ever hear of this this is a scam unscrupulous thieves have sent you this email and they are trying to part you from your hard earned cash they will often ask you to call a premium rate number and keep you holding on whilst you rack up a huge phone bill they are then paid a large proportion of this phone bill they may ask you to divulge personal information about yourself or ask for your bank or credit card details do not divulge any such information under any circumstances it is surprising how many innocent victims have been duped by these types of emails just remember the thieves who send them are very clever and extremely convincing i suggest you delete the email and send it into cyberspace hopefully along with the thieving scumbags who send them check out these sites for further information http www scambusters com http www hoax slayer com internet scams html http www police west tisbury ma us internet scams htm Advance fee fraud Phishing Internet fraud Lottery HTML HyperText Transfer Protocol Credit card Identity theft E-mail spam Neopets Gmail Bank fraud Surveillance Mail fraud Stopping e-mail abuse RuneScape cheats Web crawler Uniform Resource Locator Internet HTTP cookie Plame affair British national identity card Website World Wide Web Fraud Denial-of-service attack Virgin Mobile GSM services Make money fast Credit card fraud Password Ajax (programming) Computer virus Mail-order bride Bank MIME Slashdot subculture Common Unix Printing System Skype IP address Electronic commerce Kazaa Euro Intranet Abramoff-Reed Indian Gambling Scandal Bluetooth Transmission Control Protocol Insurance Modem Gambling United Kingdom corporation tax Google Computer Domain name Automatic teller machine Poker jargon MapleStory Web server Domain Name System Filling station Dialer Octopus card Charles Ponzi Anonymity Whois Slo